      <hedline>
        <hl1>BUS OPERATOR DEFERS DEBT PAYMENTS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Laidlaw Inc has deferred semiannual payments of $23 million on three series of debentures as it continues to negotiate new agreements with creditors (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The operator of North America's largest fleet of school and intercity buses, Laidlaw Inc. of Burlington, Ontario, has deferred semiannual payments of $23 million on three series of debentures as it continues to negotiate new agreements with creditors. Laidlaw said its operating companies, including Greyhound Lines, were not affected.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard</p>
      </block>
